1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:08,600
NEXUS Sentinel Recovery is a governed AI release incident workflow built for UiPath AgentHack Track Two, Maestro BPMN.

2
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:13,089
Enterprise AI releases do not fail in one predictable way.

3
00:00:13,089 --> 00:00:17,786
The requested model can differ from the model actually returned by a provider.

4
00:00:17,786 --> 00:00:20,457
Required evidence can be incomplete.

5
00:00:20,457 --> 00:00:24,984
A privileged remediation can be proposed without accountable approval.

6
00:00:24,984 --> 00:00:28,852
Even after remediation, verification can fail.

7
00:00:28,852 --> 00:00:37,563
A production control plane must detect each condition, stop unsafe execution, and recover without losing the process history.

8
00:00:37,563 --> 00:00:40,734
Our architecture separates authority from advice.

9
00:00:40,734 --> 00:00:45,642
UiPath Automation Cloud is the control and execution plane.

10
00:00:45,642 --> 00:00:55,444
Maestro BPMN owns the process, every gateway, the approval step, remediation, verification, rework, and closure.

11
00:00:55,444 --> 00:00:59,944
UiPath Solutions Management packages and deploys the workflow.

12
00:00:59,944 --> 00:01:04,681
Orchestrator starts the job and exposes a per-node execution trace.

13
00:01:04,681 --> 00:01:08,800
The NEXUS Sentinel Policy Adapter is deliberately narrow.

14
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,207
It never performs remediation.

15
00:01:11,207 --> 00:01:19,155
It receives structured release evidence and returns one of three deterministic verdicts: allow, hold, or deny.

16
00:01:19,155 --> 00:01:29,931
Every response includes stable reason codes, a risk level, a recommended stage, a required human role when applicable, and an audit identifier.

17
00:01:29,931 --> 00:01:37,800
Requests are strict, replay-safe, and retain only an input fingerprint plus the structured outcome in process memory.

18
00:01:37,800 --> 00:01:40,286
Here is the live BPMN process.

19
00:01:40,286 --> 00:01:46,326
An AI Release Incident moves to Evaluate Release Risk and then to the Policy Verdict gateway.

20
00:01:46,326 --> 00:01:50,431
A hold routes through the AI Release Manager Approval user task.

21
00:01:50,431 --> 00:01:54,023
Allow advances directly to bounded remediation.

22
00:01:54,023 --> 00:01:57,234
Deny terminates at Security Escalation.

23
00:01:57,234 --> 00:02:02,063
After remediation, Verify Recovery reaches a second gateway.

24
00:02:02,063 --> 00:02:05,115
Passed verification closes the process.

25
00:02:05,115 --> 00:02:10,471
Failed verification enters Rework Required and loops back to evaluation.

26
00:02:10,471 --> 00:02:14,471
This is a recovery system, not a happy-path diagram.

27
00:02:14,471 --> 00:02:18,155
The public adapter demonstrates the same contract.

28
00:02:18,155 --> 00:02:27,813
Our safety-hold sample requests one model but observes another, omits required evidence, and requests privileged remediation without approval.

29
00:02:27,813 --> 00:02:36,050
The response is hold, high risk, with model echo mismatch, evidence incomplete, and human approval required.

30
00:02:36,050 --> 00:02:40,510
The approved sample returns allow and advances to remediation.

31
00:02:40,510 --> 00:02:45,918
A failed verification returns rework required and re-entry to investigation.

32
00:02:45,918 --> 00:02:49,918
A second verification succeeds and recommends closure.

33
00:02:49,918 --> 00:02:56,694
Replaying the original request returns the same audit identifier, proving idempotent behavior.

34
00:02:56,694 --> 00:02:59,694
The UiPath artifact is not conceptual.

35
00:02:59,694 --> 00:03:03,221
Studio Web validates the model with zero issues.

36
00:03:03,221 --> 00:03:09,984
Solutions Management published package Solution One, version one point zero point zero.

37
00:03:09,984 --> 00:03:12,550
Deployment completed successfully.

38
00:03:12,550 --> 00:03:27,536
A manual Orchestrator job then executed successfully through eight trace nodes: incident, evaluation, verdict, approval, remediation, verification, verification gateway, and verified closure.

39
00:03:27,536 --> 00:03:30,273
We also state the current boundary honestly.

40
00:03:30,273 --> 00:03:38,734
The approval step is a BPMN User Task, but it is not yet bound to an Action App, so it auto-completed in this verified run.

41
00:03:38,734 --> 00:03:44,510
A live Action Center handoff is the next integration step, not a completed claim.

42
00:03:44,510 --> 00:04:00,155
The public repository includes the FastAPI adapter, four sample incidents, the portable BPMN source, UiPath Windows workflow, Apache Two license, build guide, judge matrix, and eighteen passing tests.

43
00:04:00,155 --> 00:04:07,721
Codex, Gemini, Kilo Code, and Cline contributed to implementation, review, and validation.

44
00:04:07,721 --> 00:04:25,405
NEXUS Sentinel shows how UiPath can govern external AI services without surrendering execution authority: deterministic policy evidence, explicit accountability, bounded remediation, and recoverable verification failure in one auditable enterprise workflow.

